.DS_Store

# Live test artifacts (rendered with real pod data)
tests/live/results/*.json
tests/live/results/*.png
!tests/live/results/.gitkeep

# Locally-built bundle snapshot (release artifact, ships separately — not in repo)
*.bar
oac/bundle-*.bar

# Private working notes & environment-specific scripts — kept locally only.
# These contain hardcoded cluster IDs, vault OCIDs, internal pod URLs, and
# step-level details that must NEVER be pushed to a public branch.
# Canonical home: dev/ (all PLAN/DECISION/DESIGN/RESEARCH/BOOTSTRAP files
# moved there 2026-05-17). The patterns below remain as a safety net for
# any new working notes accidentally created at the repo root.
dev/
PLAN_*.md
BLOCKER_*.md
LIMITS.md
OVERVIEW_*.md
BOOTSTRAP_*.py
FIX_*.py

# Exception: scripts/dev/ is where shipped dev tools live (e.g.
# transcribe_v1_registry.py — the v1-parity-baseline transcription tool
# used by Phase 4's dual-runner gate). The `dev/` rule above targets the
# top-level working-notes directory, not anywhere named dev.
!scripts/dev/
!scripts/dev/**
TC*_runner.py
TC_*_runner.py

# Phase 5 — diagnostic artefacts written by the readiness / drift gates
# when tests run against fixture bundles. The path comes from
# `bundle_path.resolve().parent / ".aidp" / "diagnostics"` in the
# gate helpers; the fixture-side writes are transient noise.
tests/fixtures/**/.aidp/

# local tenant coords (real OCIDs/keys) — never commit
aidp.config.yaml

# local tenant bundle (real pod URL / user / contentPack) — never commit
bundle.yaml

# local tenant profiles (bootstrap-pinned fingerprints) — never commit
profiles/

# OAC workbook authoring (workbooks/<name>/) — the generated workbook JSON and
# any *bound* request carry the OAC host / dataset UUID / session tokens. Keep
# those raw artifacts local; commit only *.redacted.json (and your request.json
# spec). See skills/workbook-authoring + docs/oac_workbook_authoring_e2e.md.
workbooks/**/workbook*.json
workbooks/**/*bound*.json
!workbooks/**/*.redacted.json
